    "The scene continues as written below."
    "Night falls like a blanket, and the promenade lights sputter into isolated islands. Police presence arrives in a few marked vehicles—shadows moving with intent. Conversations mutate into strategy. Ravi and a handful of volunteers begin a"
    "slow, organized attempt to block access to the council plaza: a human line, bodies linked. It's the kind of nonviolent direct action that asks the town to watch and to choose a side."
    "The officers move in with commands, their voices flat and procedural. People are detained with an economy of motion you've only watched in videos and training modules. There is shock because it is real; there is"
    "anger because it is political; there is a coldness in the air as flashlights pick out faces."
    "Ravi: (to you, as officers close in) 'We trained for this—document, stay calm.' (He slides a camera into someone’s hands.) 'I'll be fine—'"

    isla_morgan "Don't be reckless."
    "The guilt settles into you like silt. It is heavy and quiet and refuses to be flung off. You led the push; your hands built the reef they came to see. People cheered because they glimpsed"
    "a future; they feared because futures require sacrifices many cannot bear. You can trace a line from your compass to the point where the line meets another life being put behind bracelets of metal."
    "Jonah Merrick: (quiet, close) 'We did something honest tonight,' he says, but there is no triumph in it—only exhaustion. 'The town will judge by consequences.'"
    "You look at the band of officers, at the small group of detained neighbors, at the way faces around you have shifted into private calculations. You think of the elder fisherman, the way his lips moved"
    "as Jonah steadied him; you think of the market woman's hands. You feel the canvass of your conviction pulled taut and slightly torn."
    hide isla_morgan
    hide aria_chen
    hide jonah_merrick

